        <p>Writer and editor. BA, Oxford, 1858; BCL 1866; DCL 1872. Assistant at Bruce Castle school, 1858; head, 1868; retired in 1876 owing to illness. Became a frequent contributor to magazines such as the <hi rend="italic">Saturday Review</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Pall Mall Gazette</hi> from 1869. Published a six-volume edition of James Boswell’s life of Samuel Johnson in 1887.</p></note>
